title: For Sale:  Air Rifle Marskmanship Lessons
postcontent: I have been shooting air rifles all of my life. I was involved in competitive three position air rifle shooting for over five years. I have medals all the way up to the state level and have participated in national NRA sanctioned competitions. I also have competed in three position small bore at the national level and have experience in high power competitions as well as IDPA style events. I am wanting to teach someone the basics one on one. I enjoy teaching and introducing people to new concepts they are excited about. I will work for free within reason and only accept tips as payments. At the moment, I prefer to only give lessons to complete beginners *only* in single shot air rifles and single shot air pistols for personal self-enrichment. I am not going to teach you how to hunt. This is strictly shooting stationary paper and silhouette targets. The first and most important thing I will teach you is safety and respect for firearms. With safety always being the number one concern, I will teach how to shoot supported as well as unsupported prone, standing, and kneeling. Just as important, I will also teach techniques such as breathing, diet, pulse rate, relaxation, focus, and trigger pull. I will provide all necessary equipment unless you have equipment you would like to use. What kind of equipment you have will determine the extent of your learning experience, however there is no equipment requirement except safety glasses. The only requirement *if* of you provide equipment is that you will have a single shot air rifle with closed aperture sights that is either single pump, Co2, or PCP. No multi pump guns. I also prefer not to teach with guns that have optics because optics often fail, but if you have purchased a solid setup, we can discuss the possibilities.
